You can use [`ScheduledExecutorService`][1], which allows you to schedule the same task multiple times without using [`scheduleAtFixedRate`][2]. Here&#39;s a quick example:

    ScheduledExecutorService executorService = Executors.newScheduledThreadPool(1);
    Runnable timerTask = new Runnable() {
    	@Override
    	public void run() {
    		// Do something
    		System.out.println(&quot;Task run!&quot;);
    		// Schedule again
    		executorService.schedule(this, 15, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    	}
    };
    // Schedule
    executorService.schedule(timerTask, 15, TimeUnit.SECONDS);


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/ScheduledExecutorService.html
